    <bioghist>Family of Milton M. Perry and Leonora Sinclair Perry of Lowell, Mich. Milton M. Perry was a lawyer, the son of William R. and Mary Weeks Perry of Moscow, Mich. Leonora Sinclair Perry was the daughter of Daniel and Jane Proudfit Sinclair, probably from Jonesville, Mich.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Personal correspondence, chiefly from family members, including two letters from Milton M. Perry while a law student at the University of Michigan (1865), two letters from A. C. Vanderburgh (1865) describing conditions in Nashville, Tenn., at the close of the Civil War, and one letter from A. R. Earley (1864) describing conditions in Franklin, La.</scopecontent>
